This is my music database website!<br>
<br>
My music of choice is Jpop, anime, and doujin (indie) music. Like other genres, the artists that 
create this music overlap between the genres. Unlike most other genres, all of these songs are also used
in television shows and movies. I will collectively refer to these shows and movies as "sources".
<br>
<br>
To give you an idea, take the Pixar movies Ratatouille and The Incredibles. Both of these have soundtracks done 
by Michael Giacchino. So if I wanted to record that in a database, it would look something like this:<br><br>
Name: Ratatouille OST<br>
Artist: Michael Giacchino<br>
Source: Ratatouille<br><br>

Name: Incredibles OST<br>
Artist: Michael Giacchino<br>
Source: The Incredibles<br><br>

This should be easy to keep track of in a spreadsheet, right?<br>
<br>
However! It's not so simple with anime and jpop, since each source has opening themes and ending themes, as well as the original sound track.
Thus, when we try to draw connections between all the artists, albums, and sources, we get a mess.
